1
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:35,680
Our school has a total of 18 students.

2
00:00:35,681 --> 00:00:39,191
(In a small elementary school with just 18 students,)

3
00:00:40,291 --> 00:00:44,631
(an after-school acting class by Ms. Kim has started.)

4
00:00:45,661 --> 00:00:47,400
(The goal...)

5
00:00:47,401 --> 00:00:50,301
(is to stage a play at the school arts festival!)

6
00:00:51,631 --> 00:00:55,041
(With students who have never acted before,)

7
00:00:55,701 --> 00:00:57,971
(the acting class has begun.)

8
00:00:58,341 --> 00:00:59,341
Tae Ri.

9
00:00:59,342 --> 00:01:02,641
(Mr. Choi has joined as a helper.)

10
00:01:02,811 --> 00:01:04,151
This story is...

11
00:01:04,211 --> 00:01:07,951
(To play "The Wizard of Oz")

12
00:01:08,751 --> 00:01:11,651
(The second class)

13
00:01:12,621 --> 00:01:15,761
(What happened?)

14
00:01:16,961 --> 00:01:19,230
We'll have a break now.

15
00:01:19,231 --> 00:01:22,001
We're done with everything I prepared for the first period.

16
00:01:22,231 --> 00:01:23,771
There are even toys over here.

17
00:01:24,431 --> 00:01:26,031
You're good at drawing.

18
00:01:26,531 --> 00:01:28,440
- What is it?
- How about we color it in together?

19
00:01:28,441 --> 00:01:29,741
- Or draw together?
- Okay.

20
00:01:29,971 --> 00:01:31,041
Can you draw me?

21
00:01:31,611 --> 00:01:33,480
- I'll draw too.
- Go ahead.

22
00:01:33,481 --> 00:01:34,910
- With black.
- Draw whatever you want,

23
00:01:34,911 --> 00:01:36,340
with whichever color you want.

24
00:01:36,341 --> 00:01:37,380
(Potato Teacher wants to get along with the students.)

25
00:01:37,381 --> 00:01:39,411
- It's 3:22pm.
- Done.

26
00:01:39,711 --> 00:01:40,821
You must like soccer.

27
00:01:41,721 --> 00:01:43,620
I actually watch baseball more.

28
00:01:43,621 --> 00:01:44,651
Same here.

29
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:46,961
- Stop leaning to the side.
- Why don't we play baseball?

30
00:01:47,191 --> 00:01:48,191
- What?
- Why don't we play baseball?

31
00:01:48,192 --> 00:01:49,220
- Yes!
- Where?

32
00:01:49,221 --> 00:01:50,430
- On the field.
- Okay.

33
00:01:50,431 --> 00:01:52,030
- Okay, just for ten minutes.
- I'm in.

34
00:01:52,031 --> 00:01:53,330
It's just for ten minutes.

35
00:01:53,331 --> 00:01:54,501
- Okay.
- Good.

36
00:01:54,601 --> 00:01:56,101
Potato Teacher!

37
00:01:56,501 --> 00:01:58,071
Potato Teacher!

38
00:02:00,001 --> 00:02:02,701
Potato Teacher, can't we play hide-and-seek together?

39
00:02:02,801 --> 00:02:04,240
- Do you want to play hide-and-seek?
- Yes.

40
00:02:04,241 --> 00:02:06,010
- Let's play hide-and-seek. Come.
- Hide-and-seek!

41
00:02:06,011 --> 00:02:07,511
- Come. Let's play hide-and-seek.
- Hide-and-seek!

42
00:02:07,811 --> 00:02:09,910
- Let's go, Potato Teacher.
- Let's go.

43
00:02:09,911 --> 00:02:11,450
- Let's go, Potato Teacher.
- It will be fun.

44
00:02:11,451 --> 00:02:12,611
Can't we play baseball?

45
00:02:13,581 --> 00:02:15,081
Wait, Mr. Choi is leaving.

46
00:02:27,801 --> 00:02:30,271
Unbelievable. I'm preparing this by myself.

47
00:02:34,201 --> 00:02:37,411
(The full story)

48
00:02:38,441 --> 00:02:40,540
I think it's a good idea...

49
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:42,511
for us to make a path.

50
00:02:42,781 --> 00:02:45,480
With these chairs or something,

51
00:02:45,481 --> 00:02:46,680
let's make a path...

52
00:02:46,681 --> 00:02:48,480
- during the break.
- Okay.

53
00:02:48,481 --> 00:02:51,150
For example, Scarecrow meets here.

54
00:02:51,151 --> 00:02:52,151
(However)

55
00:02:52,152 --> 00:02:53,221
Run!

56
00:02:53,691 --> 00:02:55,960
(He forgot his promise and is running away.)

57
00:02:55,961 --> 00:02:56,991
What is it?

58
00:02:57,461 --> 00:02:58,491
Hold on.

59
00:02:59,591 --> 00:03:03,601
(In the end, Ms. Kim prepares everything by herself.)

60
00:03:06,841 --> 00:03:10,711
(Checking the safety thoroughly)

61
00:03:12,541 --> 00:03:14,781
- Let's go.
- Break's ending soon.

62
00:03:15,141 --> 00:03:17,411
Next time, bring your baseball glove.

63
00:03:17,951 --> 00:03:19,080
We can play during the break.

64
00:03:19,081 --> 00:03:20,250
- How about it?
- It's not a bad idea.

65
00:03:20,251 --> 00:03:21,450
I hate baseball.

66
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,521
Do you hate baseball?

67
00:03:22,821 --> 00:03:24,720
- What do you like, Won Jin?
- Me?

68
00:03:24,721 --> 00:03:26,961
(Sesol Hall)

69
00:03:28,091 --> 00:03:30,690
(Exhausted)

70
00:03:30,691 --> 00:03:33,090
Guys, come over here.

71
00:03:33,091 --> 00:03:34,161
Everyone!

72
00:03:34,561 --> 00:03:36,800
We've got a path right here.

73
00:03:36,801 --> 00:03:39,370
This path will turn into a journey.

74
00:03:39,371 --> 00:03:43,100
I'll explain what kind of journey it will be.

75
00:03:43,101 --> 00:03:44,241
(What kind of journey will it be?)

76
00:03:44,941 --> 00:03:47,410
The scene where the three characters meet...

77
00:03:47,411 --> 00:03:49,040
is a must.

78
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:51,751
Scarecrow, Tin Man, and Lion.

79
00:03:51,881 --> 00:03:53,880
The three of them meeting...

80
00:03:53,881 --> 00:03:55,381
will happen in one go.

81
00:03:56,381 --> 00:03:57,790
All right, students.

82
00:03:57,791 --> 00:04:00,691
Shall we choose which character you want to play?

83
00:04:00,921 --> 00:04:03,661
- I want to be the Scarecrow.
- Lion!

84
00:04:03,861 --> 00:04:05,691
- Lion!
- Lion!

85
00:04:05,991 --> 00:04:07,500
- Tin Man.
- Lion!

86
00:04:07,501 --> 00:04:09,300
- What do you want to be, Ha Yun?
- Tin Man.

87
00:04:09,301 --> 00:04:10,601
- Tin Man.
- Tin Man?

88
00:04:11,471 --> 00:04:13,901
(Today's cast of "The Wizard of Oz")

89
00:04:16,301 --> 00:04:18,670
(I wish I had a brain.)

90
00:04:18,671 --> 00:04:20,841
(Scarecrow)

91
00:04:23,681 --> 00:04:26,350
(I wish I had a heart.)

92
00:04:26,351 --> 00:04:28,481
(Tin Man)

93
00:04:31,191 --> 00:04:33,350
(I wish I had the nerve.)

94
00:04:33,351 --> 00:04:36,061
(Lion)

95
00:04:36,521 --> 00:04:39,591
Guys, what did we say Mr. Choi was going to be?

96
00:04:39,891 --> 00:04:40,930
- Guess.
- Marie.

97
00:04:40,931 --> 00:04:43,030
- Do...
- "Do" what?

98
00:04:43,031 --> 00:04:44,731
- Doraemon.
- Doraemon?

99
00:04:44,971 --> 00:04:46,471
- Incorrect.
- Dotori.

100
00:04:47,001 --> 00:04:48,570
- Dotori is incorrect.
- Do...

101
00:04:48,571 --> 00:04:50,441
- Doremi?
- Doremi is incorrect.

102
00:04:50,941 --> 00:04:52,210
- I don't know.
- It's Dorothy.

103
00:04:52,211 --> 00:04:53,211
Dorothy.

104
00:04:53,212 --> 00:04:55,710
Mr. Choi will become Dorothy...

105
00:04:55,711 --> 00:04:58,780
and visit each team...

106
00:04:58,781 --> 00:05:01,521
- That's funny.
- one at a time.

107
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:03,051
Here's the thing.

108
00:05:03,321 --> 00:05:05,050
- I want to become Dorothy again.
- Here's the thing.

109
00:05:05,051 --> 00:05:06,690
When Dorothy visits you,

110
00:05:06,691 --> 00:05:09,290
you must act.

111
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:12,490
As the Scarecrow, Tin Man, and Lion.

112
00:05:12,491 --> 00:05:14,531
That's right. You must act in your role.

113
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:18,601
Mr. Choi and I will help you out.

114
00:05:18,701 --> 00:05:21,970
First, let's discuss it as a team.

115
00:05:21,971 --> 00:05:23,001
Okay.

116
00:05:23,641 --> 00:05:24,670
The Scarecrow.

117
00:05:24,671 --> 00:05:25,811
(Roaring)

118
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:27,580
Where are you going?

119
00:05:27,581 --> 00:05:29,111
(Team Lion)

120
00:05:29,581 --> 00:05:31,310
A cat-like lion.

121
00:05:31,311 --> 00:05:32,750
(Acting the role immediately)

122
00:05:32,751 --> 00:05:34,081
- Ms. Kim.
- Again?

123
00:05:34,281 --> 00:05:35,320
- We...
- That's it. You would...

124
00:05:35,321 --> 00:05:36,720
have your arms open.

125
00:05:36,721 --> 00:05:38,091
- A cat.
- You're already a lion.

126
00:05:38,191 --> 00:05:41,120
Give me a minute. Wander around, okay?

127
00:05:41,121 --> 00:05:42,891
I'll go once I'm done with Team Scarecrow.

128
00:05:45,431 --> 00:05:47,430
(Wandering around)

129
00:05:47,431 --> 00:05:48,631
Sliding.

130
00:05:49,031 --> 00:05:50,870
Okay, what should we ask Dorothy to do...

131
00:05:50,871 --> 00:05:53,200
- once she comes here?
- Scarecrow.

132
00:05:53,201 --> 00:05:54,341
(Educating the Scarecrow's world)

133
00:05:55,441 --> 00:05:57,441
- Take me with you.
- "Take me with you?"

134
00:05:57,711 --> 00:06:00,940
But that's not possible because you're stuck on a rod.

135
00:06:00,941 --> 00:06:02,681
So what should you ask first?

136
00:06:02,981 --> 00:06:04,710
- Pull me out.
- Pull me out.

137
00:06:04,711 --> 00:06:05,711
Correct. Ask Dorothy...

138
00:06:05,712 --> 00:06:07,321
- to pull you out first.
- Pop.

139
00:06:07,481 --> 00:06:08,980
She'll help you.

140
00:06:08,981 --> 00:06:11,750
Once you're pulled out, what do you need to ask for?

141
00:06:11,751 --> 00:06:13,620
- A brain.
- Yes, a brain.

142
00:06:13,621 --> 00:06:17,431
Ask Dorothy, "Dorothy, where are you going?"

143
00:06:18,191 --> 00:06:19,290
The Lion.

144
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:20,530
(Next is Team Lion.)

145
00:06:20,531 --> 00:06:22,801
Come here, Won Jin. The Lion isn't brave.

146
00:06:23,331 --> 00:06:24,530
It's a scaredy-cat.

147
00:06:24,531 --> 00:06:26,331
What should you do when Dorothy and her friends come?

148
00:06:26,801 --> 00:06:27,971
Dorothy is here.

149
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:30,771
But once Dorothy gets here,

150
00:06:31,571 --> 00:06:33,541
she gets scared and backs away.

151
00:06:34,081 --> 00:06:36,211
The Lion gets hit on the nose.

152
00:06:36,611 --> 00:06:37,851
What happens next?

153
00:06:39,011 --> 00:06:40,280
(Acting scared is the highlight.)

154
00:06:40,281 --> 00:06:42,281
The Lion turns out to be a total coward.

155
00:06:43,551 --> 00:06:44,650
One to zero.

156
00:06:44,651 --> 00:06:47,020
(Fencing with the props)

157
00:06:47,021 --> 00:06:48,121
It's 1 to 0.

158
00:06:49,421 --> 00:06:50,460
Enough.

159
00:06:50,461 --> 00:06:51,890
Don't fight with the props.

160
00:06:51,891 --> 00:06:53,130
- We're fencing.
- All right.

161
00:06:53,131 --> 00:06:54,630
What does the Tin Man say...

162
00:06:54,631 --> 00:06:57,000
as soon as Dorothy gets here?

163
00:06:57,001 --> 00:06:58,570
(If I touch water, I rust. Then, I can't move. You have to oil me.)

164
00:06:58,571 --> 00:07:00,470
- I can't talk.
- You can't, right?

165
00:07:00,471 --> 00:07:02,570
- No.
- But you must.

166
00:07:02,571 --> 00:07:03,940
How would you say?

167
00:07:03,941 --> 00:07:05,171
You can't move your jaw.

168
00:07:05,811 --> 00:07:07,611
- You can't move your jaw.
- Oil?

169
00:07:07,741 --> 00:07:09,341
Correct.

170
00:07:09,481 --> 00:07:10,580
I'll wear it like this.

171
00:07:10,581 --> 00:07:12,280
I'll be watching you two when Dorothy gets here.

172
00:07:12,281 --> 00:07:13,311
- Got it?
- Yes.

173
00:07:13,621 --> 00:07:15,681
- Lions.
- Lions, gather.

174
00:07:16,521 --> 00:07:18,090
- Do Hyun, go back.
- Back to your spot, Lions.

175
00:07:18,091 --> 00:07:19,091
That was a nice nap.

176
00:07:19,351 --> 00:07:23,061
The story starts with Dorothy.

177
00:07:23,691 --> 00:07:28,160
Dorothy's house flies away because of a whirlwind, right?

178
00:07:28,161 --> 00:07:31,331
Dorothy's house lands in an unknown place.

179
00:07:31,831 --> 00:07:34,341
It turns out to be a whole new world.

180
00:07:34,971 --> 00:07:37,940
Some people gather around her and say,

181
00:07:37,941 --> 00:07:39,341
(A heartfelt welcome from the Oz villagers)

182
00:07:39,471 --> 00:07:43,181
"Your house just crushed the Witch..."

183
00:07:43,541 --> 00:07:45,951
"who has been bullying us all along!"

184
00:07:46,481 --> 00:07:48,681
"We're free now!"

185
00:07:48,821 --> 00:07:50,790
(Starting to act)

186
00:07:50,791 --> 00:07:52,051
But why are you crying?

187
00:07:52,421 --> 00:07:53,990
I want to go home.

188
00:07:53,991 --> 00:07:55,521
If you want to go home,

189
00:07:55,791 --> 00:07:58,290
how about visiting the Wizard of Oz?

190
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:00,061
- The Wizard of Oz?
- Yes.

191
00:08:00,661 --> 00:08:03,261
Where must I go to meet the Wizard of Oz?

192
00:08:03,431 --> 00:08:06,801
The Wizard of Oz is the strongest in this world.

193
00:08:06,971 --> 00:08:09,340
You must travel a long distance...

194
00:08:09,341 --> 00:08:12,111
to meet him.

195
00:08:12,371 --> 00:08:14,510
- Okay, I think I can do it.
- Good.

196
00:08:14,511 --> 00:08:17,280
With that, Dorothy sets off on a journey.

197
00:08:17,281 --> 00:08:19,281
(Dorothy sets off on a journey.)

198
00:08:20,451 --> 00:08:23,521
I, Dorothy, will meet the Wizard of Oz...

199
00:08:23,921 --> 00:08:25,451
and get my house back!

200
00:08:27,021 --> 00:08:28,091
How tiresome.

201
00:08:28,221 --> 00:08:29,260
(Struggling)

202
00:08:29,261 --> 00:08:30,631
I can see the mountains.

203
00:08:30,861 --> 00:08:32,761
It sure is beautiful.

204
00:08:32,831 --> 00:08:34,701
I've always dreamed of such a place.

205
00:08:34,961 --> 00:08:39,201
But I will meet the Wizard of Oz and tell him what I must.

206
00:08:40,801 --> 00:08:41,870
I'm exhausted.

207
00:08:41,871 --> 00:08:43,101
(The first friend she encounters on the journey)

208
00:08:43,741 --> 00:08:45,341
There are scarecrows here.

209
00:08:45,841 --> 00:08:48,011
Scarecrows, what do you want to ask for?

210
00:08:48,311 --> 00:08:50,111
Where are you going?

211
00:08:50,181 --> 00:08:53,051
I'm going to see the Wizard of Oz...

212
00:08:53,251 --> 00:08:55,351
and ask for my house.

213
00:08:56,451 --> 00:08:58,221
By the way, are you okay?

214
00:08:58,851 --> 00:09:00,861
- Pull me out, please.
- Why?

215
00:09:01,321 --> 00:09:03,120
I can't move.

216
00:09:03,121 --> 00:09:04,731
Once I pull you out,

217
00:09:04,791 --> 00:09:08,461
how about we go together to meet the Wizard of Oz?

218
00:09:08,901 --> 00:09:10,301
- Okay.
- Before that,

219
00:09:11,431 --> 00:09:12,671
doesn't your head hurt?

220
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:17,040
Because Dorothy is kind-hearted,

221
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,340
she's worried about the Scarecrow.

222
00:09:19,341 --> 00:09:20,511
Come with me.

223
00:09:20,811 --> 00:09:21,910
Let's cheer.

224
00:09:21,911 --> 00:09:24,381
"Let's go to the Wizard of Oz," okay?

225
00:09:24,451 --> 00:09:25,550
In 1, 2, 3.

226
00:09:25,551 --> 00:09:26,651
Let's...

227
00:09:26,851 --> 00:09:27,981
Let's go.

228
00:09:28,951 --> 00:09:29,951
- Hurry.
- All right.

229
00:09:29,952 --> 00:09:31,590
Standby, Tin Men.

230
00:09:31,591 --> 00:09:32,950
Let's go.

231
00:09:32,951 --> 00:09:34,520
That's it.

232
00:09:34,521 --> 00:09:36,621
You're stiff. You can't move.

233
00:09:36,761 --> 00:09:37,761
- You can't...
- Can I not move...

234
00:09:37,761 --> 00:09:38,761
because I'm not oiled up?

235
00:09:38,762 --> 00:09:39,860
Correct. Wait for a second.

236
00:09:39,861 --> 00:09:42,430
Just when we're all happy...

237
00:09:42,431 --> 00:09:43,461
Stop right there.

238
00:09:43,661 --> 00:09:46,371
You can hear something groaning.

239
00:09:47,031 --> 00:09:48,971
You can hear something groaning.

240
00:09:49,201 --> 00:09:50,571
Oil.

241
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:51,970
What was that? Listen to them.

242
00:09:51,971 --> 00:09:53,810
The Tin Man is saying something.

243
00:09:53,811 --> 00:09:55,381
- Listen to them.
- Oil.

244
00:09:55,981 --> 00:09:57,311
- What?
- Oil.

245
00:09:57,511 --> 00:09:58,651
- What?
- Oil.

246
00:09:58,851 --> 00:10:01,021
- What?
- Oil.

247
00:10:02,581 --> 00:10:04,150
(Tin Man Ha Yun is all rusty.)

248
00:10:04,151 --> 00:10:05,821
- Oil?
- Oil!

249
00:10:06,151 --> 00:10:08,190
- Oil?
- They need oil.

250
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,191
We have to oil them.

251
00:10:09,191 --> 00:10:10,191
- Dorothy.
- Yes?

252
00:10:10,192 --> 00:10:12,060
An oil drum is right here.

253
00:10:12,061 --> 00:10:13,091
- An oil drum?
- Here.

254
00:10:15,261 --> 00:10:17,000
Help me move this oil drum.

255
00:10:17,001 --> 00:10:19,000
The Scarecrows help Dorothy oil...

256
00:10:19,001 --> 00:10:20,640
- Let's oil them.
- Go for it.

257
00:10:20,641 --> 00:10:22,640
- Pour it on them.
- They poured it on them.

258
00:10:22,641 --> 00:10:23,740
Pour it on them.

259
00:10:23,741 --> 00:10:25,310
- I'm up.
- Are you?

260
00:10:25,311 --> 00:10:27,111
They poured the oil on them.

261
00:10:27,411 --> 00:10:30,310
Don't you wish for a heart or something?

262
00:10:30,311 --> 00:10:32,250
- Yes.
- Yes, our heart...

263
00:10:32,251 --> 00:10:35,221
I don't have a heart and don't know how to fight.

264
00:10:35,421 --> 00:10:36,951
Join us, okay?

265
00:10:37,191 --> 00:10:38,550
(Even the Tin Men join them.)

266
00:10:38,551 --> 00:10:41,390
Dorothy has made many friends.

267
00:10:41,391 --> 00:10:43,491
- Oh, dear.
- Come.

268
00:10:44,131 --> 00:10:45,191
Hold on.

269
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:47,161
- Isn't this...
- Isn't this...

270
00:10:47,961 --> 00:10:50,201
- Something sounds scary.
- It's...

271
00:10:50,571 --> 00:10:51,631
No!

272
00:10:51,771 --> 00:10:53,731
(The Tin Man scolds the Lion.)

273
00:10:54,441 --> 00:10:58,070
Tin Men, the Lion is a scary being.

274
00:10:58,071 --> 00:11:00,041
- Everyone, the Lions.
- Lions.

275
00:11:00,411 --> 00:11:03,540
The Lions are crying.

276
00:11:03,541 --> 00:11:05,050
- The Lions...
- Did you just cut my tail?

277
00:11:05,051 --> 00:11:06,351
The Lion took my...

278
00:11:06,811 --> 00:11:08,121
Help me. The Lion is...

279
00:11:08,551 --> 00:11:09,551
(Laughing)

280
00:11:09,552 --> 00:11:11,520
The Lion has revived.

281
00:11:11,521 --> 00:11:12,820
(Walking out of rage)

282
00:11:12,821 --> 00:11:14,261
- No, stop.
- Hold on.

283
00:11:16,421 --> 00:11:18,861
That's not how you use the axe, okay?

284
00:11:19,061 --> 00:11:21,400
Lions can't hold an axe.

285
00:11:21,401 --> 00:11:22,531
- Okay.
- Got it?

286
00:11:22,731 --> 00:11:26,801
All right, last but not least, even the Lions became friends.

287
00:11:26,901 --> 00:11:29,700
Everyone will travel together...

288
00:11:29,701 --> 00:11:32,941
to meet the Wizard of Oz.

289
00:11:33,511 --> 00:11:34,841
Well done.

290
00:11:35,411 --> 00:11:39,611
In the next part of the story, a Witch appears on the way...

291
00:11:40,521 --> 00:11:42,251
to find the Wizard of Oz.

292
00:11:42,381 --> 00:11:46,850
Remember how Dorothy's house landed on top of a Witch?

293
00:11:46,851 --> 00:11:47,961
That Witch...

294
00:11:48,661 --> 00:11:52,131
turns out to be the younger sister of a very wicked Witch.

295
00:11:52,561 --> 00:11:55,061
The Wicked Witch...

296
00:11:55,431 --> 00:11:57,401
attacks Dorothy.

297
00:11:58,131 --> 00:12:01,900
But Dorothy already has many friends, right?

298
00:12:01,901 --> 00:12:05,241
Everyone works together and defeats the Witch.

299
00:12:05,941 --> 00:12:09,211
With that, they finally meet the Wizard of Oz.

300
00:12:09,381 --> 00:12:13,051
When they do, they make a wish to the Wizard of Oz.

301
00:12:13,151 --> 00:12:16,051
That's the whole story of "The Wizard of Oz,"

302
00:12:16,751 --> 00:12:18,691
which we'll perform on November 11.

303
00:12:19,091 --> 00:12:22,460
We're having an outdoor class tomorrow.

304
00:12:22,461 --> 00:12:24,361
(Tomorrow is an outdoor class.)

305
00:12:25,391 --> 00:12:29,531
We're going to ride in a car out of the school...

306
00:12:29,631 --> 00:12:34,041
and have lunch that Potato Teacher will make for us.

307
00:12:34,541 --> 00:12:36,341
- Guys.
- I have a question.

308
00:12:37,101 --> 00:12:38,840
What do you like the most?

309
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:40,581
- Ramyeon.
- Ramyeon.

310
00:12:40,841 --> 00:12:42,110
Rolled omelet.

311
00:12:42,111 --> 00:12:43,280
(Eun Soo likes rolled omelet.)

312
00:12:43,281 --> 00:12:44,981
- Tuna gimbap.
- Sounds nice.

313
00:12:45,111 --> 00:12:47,011
- He has 3.
- What are the 3?

314
00:12:47,251 --> 00:12:49,981
Korean food, fast food, and malatang.

315
00:12:52,251 --> 00:12:53,291
How old are you?

316
00:12:53,751 --> 00:12:55,420
Ms. Kim!

317
00:12:55,421 --> 00:12:57,691
I think he lied about his age.

318
00:12:58,461 --> 00:13:00,460
It felt like a dream.

319
00:13:00,461 --> 00:13:01,461
(How was your first class?)

320
00:13:01,462 --> 00:13:04,801
They were so cute in my first class.

321
00:13:05,601 --> 00:13:06,731
They were lovely.

322
00:13:06,971 --> 00:13:10,001
I haven't felt that energy in so long.

323
00:13:11,671 --> 00:13:13,771
See you at tomorrow's outdoor class.

324
00:13:14,881 --> 00:13:15,940
I don't want to go home.

325
00:13:15,941 --> 00:13:17,651
I'd have to do homework.

326
00:13:18,711 --> 00:13:20,011
I don't have any homework.

327
00:13:20,721 --> 00:13:21,721
Lucky you.

328
00:13:22,951 --> 00:13:25,621
- Bye!
- Bye, Ms. Kim.

329
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,190
- Bye, Ms. Kim.
- Bye.

330
00:13:27,191 --> 00:13:28,290
See you at tomorrow's outdoor class!

331
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:29,321
Sure.

332
00:13:32,091 --> 00:13:35,401
(Once the kids are gone,)

333
00:13:37,971 --> 00:13:40,500
(the classroom gets quiet.)

334
00:13:40,501 --> 00:13:41,571
Good work, Ms. Kim.

335
00:13:42,141 --> 00:13:43,201
Good work.

336
00:13:43,241 --> 00:13:44,711
That was...

337
00:13:45,171 --> 00:13:49,581
(Worn out)

338
00:13:51,951 --> 00:13:53,151
Now, clean this up.

339
00:13:54,251 --> 00:13:55,251
Start.

340
00:13:57,151 --> 00:13:58,151
Clean it up.

341
00:13:58,421 --> 00:14:01,091
I want to get some rest.

342
00:14:03,161 --> 00:14:06,561
(Going on a strike)

343
00:14:07,431 --> 00:14:08,931
- That was so tough.
- Hey.

344
00:14:10,671 --> 00:14:12,301
My mouth tastes weird.

345
00:14:16,101 --> 00:14:17,371
I'm starving.

346
00:14:18,211 --> 00:14:19,670
- Let's eat something tasty.
- What should we eat?

347
00:14:19,671 --> 00:14:21,480
Something delicious. I don't feel like cooking.

348
00:14:21,481 --> 00:14:23,910
I just want to go outside...

349
00:14:23,911 --> 00:14:25,850
- Yes, let's eat out.
- and eat delicious food.

350
00:14:25,851 --> 00:14:27,981
We need to eat gochujang pork belly.

351
00:14:28,581 --> 00:14:30,151
- Should we leave?
- Yes.

352
00:14:31,051 --> 00:14:32,121
Let's eat first.

353
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:33,951
Let's get going.

354
00:14:35,461 --> 00:14:36,991
What did you do with them outside?

355
00:14:37,321 --> 00:14:39,791
- We played hide-and-seek.
- Seriously?

356
00:14:41,131 --> 00:14:42,231
Let's go.

357
00:14:42,331 --> 00:14:43,830
I'll drive.

358
00:14:43,831 --> 00:14:45,001
Yes!

359
00:14:47,441 --> 00:14:49,101
Won Jin is so cute.

360
00:14:49,441 --> 00:14:50,911
He is, isn't he?

361
00:14:51,241 --> 00:14:53,510
- And he's like a middle-aged man.
- Is he?

362
00:14:53,511 --> 00:14:55,911
He likes Korean food, fast food, and malatang.

363
00:14:58,211 --> 00:14:59,750
Oh, my gosh!

364
00:14:59,751 --> 00:15:02,550
(They find a kitten in front of the restaurant.)

365
00:15:02,551 --> 00:15:03,581
There's a cat.

366
00:15:03,781 --> 00:15:06,151
(Scuttling)

367
00:15:07,991 --> 00:15:10,021
It must have been born here. Right?

368
00:15:10,121 --> 00:15:11,161
Yes.

369
00:15:11,391 --> 00:15:12,631
Hi.

370
00:15:13,731 --> 00:15:14,731
(This cat owner can't keep her eyes off.)

371
00:15:14,732 --> 00:15:15,801
Adorable.

372
00:15:16,931 --> 00:15:18,231
- Hello.
- Hello.

373
00:15:18,331 --> 00:15:19,400
- Come on in.
- Okay.

374
00:15:19,401 --> 00:15:20,401
(Enjoy your food.)

375
00:15:21,271 --> 00:15:22,971
I bet it tastes good.

376
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:27,681
I'm starving.

377
00:15:29,511 --> 00:15:30,981
I could eat two bowls of rice.

378
00:15:34,281 --> 00:15:35,481
I might fall asleep after I eat.

379
00:15:36,251 --> 00:15:37,991
If you could go to sleep without having to do anything,

380
00:15:38,191 --> 00:15:39,951
how long would you sleep?

381
00:15:41,921 --> 00:15:44,361
(Happy)

382
00:15:45,331 --> 00:15:47,161
Let's decide on what food to bring.

383
00:15:47,761 --> 00:15:49,600
It could be gimbap or kimchi fried rice.

384
00:15:49,601 --> 00:15:50,931
Something they could share.

385
00:15:51,501 --> 00:15:52,731
That's my personal opinion.

386
00:15:53,371 --> 00:15:54,500
Kimchi fried rice?

387
00:15:54,501 --> 00:15:56,940
- Or a rice ball...
- Should we make it...

388
00:15:56,941 --> 00:15:58,470
- with tuna and mayo.
- with meat?

389
00:15:58,471 --> 00:16:00,981
We could use fried kimchi.

390
00:16:01,911 --> 00:16:03,681
So, you want rice balls instead of gimbap?

391
00:16:04,681 --> 00:16:06,010
Gimbap and rice balls.

392
00:16:06,011 --> 00:16:07,451
Gimbap and rice balls?

393
00:16:08,381 --> 00:16:09,951
The side dishes that we bought...

394
00:16:10,821 --> 00:16:11,990
Or rolled omelets.

395
00:16:11,991 --> 00:16:13,751
(Or rolled omelets that Eun Soo likes?)

396
00:16:13,951 --> 00:16:14,961
Braised tofu.

397
00:16:16,061 --> 00:16:18,261
Or stir-fried mushrooms.

398
00:16:19,031 --> 00:16:20,290
Or musubi.

399
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:22,000
(Musubi? Stir-fried mushrooms? Braised tofu?)

400
00:16:22,001 --> 00:16:24,771
Rolled omelets, nuggets, and gimbap.

401
00:16:25,331 --> 00:16:27,130
I think that's enough.

402
00:16:27,131 --> 00:16:29,871
And a little bit of fruit on the side.

403
00:16:31,911 --> 00:16:34,711
Glazed crispy chicken would be great.

404
00:16:35,381 --> 00:16:36,711
Kids would love that.

405
00:16:36,911 --> 00:16:38,681
How would we make glazed crispy chicken?

406
00:16:39,611 --> 00:16:40,651
Exactly.

407
00:16:42,351 --> 00:16:43,480
We got nuggets.

408
00:16:43,481 --> 00:16:45,350
- Yes, nuggets will do.
- Yes.

409
00:16:45,351 --> 00:16:46,351
(Potato Teacher has a lot he wants to do.)

410
00:16:47,991 --> 00:16:49,361
Amazing.

411
00:16:49,461 --> 00:16:51,131
- Here's your food.
- Put it at the center.

412
00:16:52,691 --> 00:16:54,130
Awesome.

413
00:16:54,131 --> 00:16:56,130
- Enjoy your food.
- Thank you, sir.

414
00:16:56,131 --> 00:16:57,331
(Stir-fried pork)

415
00:16:59,531 --> 00:17:02,501
(He quickly takes a bite.)

416
00:17:04,241 --> 00:17:05,541
It's so good.

417
00:17:12,951 --> 00:17:15,321
(She neatly makes a wrap and eats it.)

418
00:17:16,881 --> 00:17:18,020
This is the main dish.

419
00:17:18,021 --> 00:17:19,720
(The main dish arrives.)

420
00:17:19,721 --> 00:17:22,020
Oh, my gosh. Thank you.

421
00:17:22,021 --> 00:17:24,531
(Yakdol pork belly)

422
00:17:25,231 --> 00:17:26,691
We should teach them that.

423
00:17:26,891 --> 00:17:29,960
- We have to enunciate, right?
- Yes.

424
00:17:29,961 --> 00:17:32,631
Instead of going, "Let's go, hooray,"

425
00:17:32,731 --> 00:17:35,101
we can make them enunciate it.

426
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:37,071
What do you think is different...

427
00:17:39,341 --> 00:17:40,411
about this pork?

428
00:17:42,911 --> 00:17:44,140
- Hyun Wook.
- Yes?

429
00:17:44,141 --> 00:17:46,581
When I just said that about our class,

430
00:17:46,681 --> 00:17:47,781
what were you thinking?

431
00:17:48,781 --> 00:17:50,221
"This pork belly looks tasty."

432
00:17:50,721 --> 00:17:52,751
The meat that's in front of me always comes first.

433
00:17:55,261 --> 00:17:58,091
I think the assistant teacher's jobs are...

434
00:17:58,191 --> 00:17:59,930
Yes, please tell me.

435
00:17:59,931 --> 00:18:01,461
I'm the main teacher,

436
00:18:01,561 --> 00:18:04,730
and I say, "I think our class needs..."

437
00:18:04,731 --> 00:18:05,930
"this and that,"

438
00:18:05,931 --> 00:18:07,841
then you should go, "We should think about that."

439
00:18:07,941 --> 00:18:09,141
I am thinking.

440
00:18:10,501 --> 00:18:12,141
I was thinking, but...

441
00:18:12,241 --> 00:18:14,070
Are you asking me for more ideas?

442
00:18:14,071 --> 00:18:15,111
Yes!

443
00:18:15,441 --> 00:18:18,380
You just turn off that side of the brain.

444
00:18:18,381 --> 00:18:19,381
That's what I think.

445
00:18:19,382 --> 00:18:20,880
No, I haven't turned it off.

446
00:18:20,881 --> 00:18:22,021
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

447
00:18:22,881 --> 00:18:24,291
To be frank, it's off right now.

448
00:18:27,091 --> 00:18:28,161
I guess it's true.

449
00:18:28,921 --> 00:18:30,621
And I'm overwhelmed with the box lunches.

450
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:33,891
I'm serious.

451
00:18:34,701 --> 00:18:37,431
I was thinking about the whole process.

452
00:18:37,531 --> 00:18:38,531
Listen, Hyun Wook.

453
00:18:39,101 --> 00:18:40,770
Your passion...

454
00:18:40,771 --> 00:18:42,240
- for box lunches.
- Yes.

455
00:18:42,241 --> 00:18:45,370
You know? You're like, "What do you think about this?"

456
00:18:45,371 --> 00:18:47,710
"Oh, glazed crispy chicken."

457
00:18:47,711 --> 00:18:49,040
That was a great example.

458
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:51,211
"Glazed crispy chicken would be great."

459
00:18:51,311 --> 00:18:52,710
"But that's too hard to make."

460
00:18:52,711 --> 00:18:54,651
"You're right, that's the problem."

461
00:18:55,051 --> 00:18:57,250
- You said that was my role.
- You use that...

462
00:18:57,251 --> 00:18:58,921
I have to cook that.

463
00:18:59,451 --> 00:19:00,890
- But...
- I think it's also important...

464
00:19:00,891 --> 00:19:02,220
to make their box lunches.

465
00:19:02,221 --> 00:19:04,021
What I'm saying is...

466
00:19:04,121 --> 00:19:05,860
you could do that in our acting class.

467
00:19:05,861 --> 00:19:09,560
You really care and are passionate...

468
00:19:09,561 --> 00:19:12,700
about their box lunches.

469
00:19:12,701 --> 00:19:15,000
And you try to come up with many ideas.

470
00:19:15,001 --> 00:19:18,841
I want you to use that much energy in acting class.

471
00:19:19,711 --> 00:19:20,711
Am I wrong?

472
00:19:21,781 --> 00:19:23,041
Are you scolding me?

473
00:19:25,311 --> 00:19:26,810
I'm just curious.

474
00:19:26,811 --> 00:19:28,521
(He cheerfully asks.)

475
00:19:29,081 --> 00:19:32,650
I thought we had meaningful results today.

476
00:19:32,651 --> 00:19:33,991
- What?
- I thought...

477
00:19:35,091 --> 00:19:36,560
(That's not what I mean.)

478
00:19:36,561 --> 00:19:37,660
As an assistant teacher...

479
00:19:37,661 --> 00:19:39,890
I don't mean that you did poorly today.

480
00:19:39,891 --> 00:19:41,900
So, what I'm saying is...

481
00:19:41,901 --> 00:19:43,600
- I'm saying this to cheer...
- Why are you bringing this up...

482
00:19:43,601 --> 00:19:44,601
- each other up.
- during a meal?

483
00:19:44,602 --> 00:19:46,371
Why are you bringing it up while we're eating?

484
00:19:46,471 --> 00:19:49,101
I just want to focus on eating when I'm eating.

485
00:19:49,201 --> 00:19:51,841
You're going to give me an upset stomach.

486
00:19:51,941 --> 00:19:53,510
When I say stuff like this, do you feel...

487
00:19:53,511 --> 00:19:54,540
like getting an upset stomach?

488
00:19:54,541 --> 00:19:56,881
It's better to finish the food quickly and talk about it.

489
00:19:58,081 --> 00:19:59,611
Okay.

490
00:20:00,151 --> 00:20:01,380
That's what I think.

491
00:20:01,381 --> 00:20:02,580
- Let's eat.
- It's...

492
00:20:02,581 --> 00:20:03,850
Let's eat.

493
00:20:03,851 --> 00:20:04,851
(She finds him cute.)

494
00:20:05,791 --> 00:20:08,991
You know, your questions, right?

495
00:20:09,091 --> 00:20:11,231
- Yes.
- I think...

496
00:20:11,331 --> 00:20:13,631
I'm more curious about other stuff.

497
00:20:14,401 --> 00:20:16,601
Like, "Will the kids read the script by tomorrow?"

498
00:20:17,101 --> 00:20:19,401
- Right.
- "Will they enjoy it?"

499
00:20:19,901 --> 00:20:22,370
- That's what I'm curious about.
- Okay.

500
00:20:22,371 --> 00:20:25,670
Also, I try to notice things...

501
00:20:25,671 --> 00:20:26,671
that you're missing.

502
00:20:26,672 --> 00:20:29,411
I calmly think and observe first.

503
00:20:29,811 --> 00:20:31,611
- Really?
- Of course, I also miss things.

504
00:20:31,711 --> 00:20:34,881
I believe that's the job of an assistant teacher.

505
00:20:34,981 --> 00:20:35,981
Yes.

506
00:20:36,081 --> 00:20:38,821
I think we had very different views on these children...

507
00:20:39,151 --> 00:20:41,191
from the get-go.

508
00:20:41,561 --> 00:20:42,761
I'm the teacher,

509
00:20:43,121 --> 00:20:46,931
and I'm more focused on what we should do...

510
00:20:47,031 --> 00:20:50,501
to successfully perform a play...

511
00:20:50,601 --> 00:20:52,700
in the end.

512
00:20:52,701 --> 00:20:53,900
But Hyun Wook tries...

513
00:20:53,901 --> 00:20:56,300
to meet them...

514
00:20:56,301 --> 00:20:58,111
at eye level.

515
00:20:58,671 --> 00:20:59,841
Aren't we really different?

516
00:21:00,711 --> 00:21:02,481
I think we are. I was surprised.

517
00:21:03,481 --> 00:21:04,680
I didn't know how different we'd be.

518
00:21:04,681 --> 00:21:07,551
Her different thoughts surprised me.

519
00:21:09,251 --> 00:21:11,321
- It's fun.
- So, that's all.

520
00:21:11,421 --> 00:21:12,421
It really is.

521
00:21:12,421 --> 00:21:13,421
(They finally realized how different they were.)

522
00:21:20,531 --> 00:21:22,701
(Good morning.)

523
00:21:26,331 --> 00:21:29,640
(Difference is not a reason for division,)

524
00:21:29,641 --> 00:21:32,971
(but an opportunity to understand one another.)

525
00:21:35,411 --> 00:21:38,811
(Tae Ri is sound asleep.)

526
00:21:39,611 --> 00:21:42,621
(Hyun Wook is already up.)

527
00:21:43,021 --> 00:21:46,391
Should I wake her up? I don't know anymore.

528
00:21:52,791 --> 00:21:56,000
(Music playing)

529
00:21:56,001 --> 00:21:57,661
(Good morning)

530
00:22:05,671 --> 00:22:07,510
(She wonders what's going on.)

531
00:22:07,511 --> 00:22:09,440
- Tae Ri!
- Yes?

532
00:22:09,441 --> 00:22:10,511
You have to get up.

533
00:22:11,351 --> 00:22:15,481
You use the worst morning alarm.

534
00:22:16,081 --> 00:22:17,351
I found it on YouTube.

535
00:22:18,851 --> 00:22:20,021
Wake up.

536
00:22:20,121 --> 00:22:21,160
I am up.

537
00:22:21,161 --> 00:22:22,591
(She's up, thanks to him.)

538
00:22:31,501 --> 00:22:32,571
Hi.

539
00:22:33,301 --> 00:22:36,640
Good morning.

540
00:22:36,641 --> 00:22:39,041
(The reason they're up so early)

541
00:22:40,011 --> 00:22:41,041
I'll start cooking.

542
00:22:41,241 --> 00:22:43,080
I'll cook rice and the rolled omelets.

543
00:22:43,081 --> 00:22:44,081
Okay.

544
00:22:44,081 --> 00:22:45,081
(Making box lunches for the outdoor class)

545
00:22:46,481 --> 00:22:48,651
(Cleanliness first)

546
00:22:49,881 --> 00:22:51,491
I could blanch them and put them on one side, right?

547
00:22:52,291 --> 00:22:53,751
Follow your dream.

548
00:22:56,091 --> 00:22:58,361
(Last night)

549
00:22:58,631 --> 00:22:59,761
I'll blanch them tomorrow.

550
00:22:59,791 --> 00:23:02,661
(They trimmed the ingredients the night before.)

551
00:23:03,931 --> 00:23:05,871
(Main chef, Choi Hyun Wook)

552
00:23:06,631 --> 00:23:09,701
(Stir-frying the ingredients)

553
00:23:11,911 --> 00:23:13,741
It looks pretty good!

554
00:23:14,441 --> 00:23:15,441
That looks great.

555
00:23:15,442 --> 00:23:16,541
(Once the rice is cooked,)

556
00:23:16,641 --> 00:23:17,840
It already smells delicious.

557
00:23:17,841 --> 00:23:19,580
(they're ready to make gimbap.)

558
00:23:19,581 --> 00:23:20,951
Let's start rolling.

559
00:23:23,581 --> 00:23:25,650
(Potato Teacher's first roll of gimbap)

560
00:23:25,651 --> 00:23:27,351
- The rice is so firm, isn't it?
- Yes.

561
00:23:27,821 --> 00:23:28,861
It's nicely cooked.

562
00:23:32,491 --> 00:23:34,461
I hope they enjoy it.

563
00:23:35,261 --> 00:23:37,001
It looks really good.

564
00:23:38,031 --> 00:23:40,100
Now, we just put...

565
00:23:40,101 --> 00:23:42,370
whatever ingredients we want.

566
00:23:42,371 --> 00:23:43,441
(Putting a bunch of ingredients)

567
00:23:46,371 --> 00:23:48,641
(Shaking)

568
00:23:50,081 --> 00:23:52,511
(He rolls his first gimbap with confidence.)

569
00:23:54,151 --> 00:23:56,081
(It opens up right away.)

570
00:23:59,351 --> 00:24:01,721
(Restless)

571
00:24:05,131 --> 00:24:07,491
Is this okay? I rolled one.

572
00:24:09,231 --> 00:24:11,971
(He tries cutting it.)

573
00:24:12,671 --> 00:24:14,971
(Opening)

574
00:24:15,471 --> 00:24:16,771
It opened up.

575
00:24:21,841 --> 00:24:26,381
(He safely puts it in his mouth.)

576
00:24:29,681 --> 00:24:32,220
(Stepping up the effort)

577
00:24:32,221 --> 00:24:33,221
(He fails.)

578
00:24:33,222 --> 00:24:34,291
Tae Ri,

579
00:24:35,091 --> 00:24:36,891
I failed one roll.

580
00:24:38,461 --> 00:24:39,661
- Let's eat it.
- But it's tasty.

581
00:24:48,341 --> 00:24:49,540
- It's good, right?
- Yes.

582
00:24:49,541 --> 00:24:50,601
(The taste is approved.)

583
00:24:51,141 --> 00:24:52,141
Again.

584
00:24:52,141 --> 00:24:53,141
(It's a success unless it falls apart.)

585
00:24:53,142 --> 00:24:54,211
I think I can do it.

586
00:24:57,541 --> 00:24:59,211
This might sound random,

587
00:25:01,251 --> 00:25:03,121
but is this what it feels like to have kids?

588
00:25:05,751 --> 00:25:07,520
(Scoffing)

589
00:25:07,521 --> 00:25:08,521
I just...

590
00:25:08,621 --> 00:25:10,021
suddenly...

591
00:25:10,291 --> 00:25:11,531
- Seriously?
- Yes.

592
00:25:11,891 --> 00:25:12,931
Really?

593
00:25:14,261 --> 00:25:15,361
The sense of responsibility.

594
00:25:16,031 --> 00:25:17,101
Really?

595
00:25:17,831 --> 00:25:20,331
But you've always wanted a child, so...

596
00:25:21,371 --> 00:25:23,471
Have I said that to you?

597
00:25:23,941 --> 00:25:25,071
I don't recall.

598
00:25:28,881 --> 00:25:31,550
All the ingredients are too high up.

599
00:25:31,551 --> 00:25:35,121
(As if he's making them for his children)

600
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:36,981
Please.

601
00:25:40,921 --> 00:25:44,321
(A father's challenge)

602
00:25:48,231 --> 00:25:50,001
Maybe there's not enough rice.

603
00:25:51,831 --> 00:25:53,531
(Neat)

604
00:25:54,571 --> 00:25:56,801
(The true father tastes it.)

605
00:25:58,311 --> 00:25:59,311
I did it!

606
00:26:00,041 --> 00:26:01,270
What kind of gimbap is that?

607
00:26:01,271 --> 00:26:02,811
- Tuna.
- Tuna?

608
00:26:05,151 --> 00:26:07,081
(Precious)

609
00:26:07,451 --> 00:26:08,580
That's amazing.

610
00:26:08,581 --> 00:26:09,680
(Gimbap made with fatherly love)

611
00:26:09,681 --> 00:26:11,721
I should start making the rolled omelets.

612
00:26:12,521 --> 00:26:13,551
You've got this, right?

613
00:26:13,951 --> 00:26:16,761
(She starts cooking rolled omelets.)

614
00:26:18,791 --> 00:26:21,931
(She adds chopped chives.)

615
00:26:23,001 --> 00:26:24,001
I can do this!

616
00:26:25,371 --> 00:26:27,901
(She starts with a shout.)

617
00:26:32,271 --> 00:26:33,370
I'm actually terrified.

618
00:26:33,371 --> 00:26:35,211
I rarely succeeded in making a rolled omelet.

619
00:26:36,381 --> 00:26:37,411
Why is it splattering already?

620
00:26:38,151 --> 00:26:39,311
It split open.

621
00:26:40,451 --> 00:26:41,451
(Sighing)

622
00:26:42,421 --> 00:26:43,421
I'm in trouble.

623
00:26:45,351 --> 00:26:47,021
Let's eat the broken ones.

624
00:26:47,551 --> 00:26:48,820
Sure.

625
00:26:48,821 --> 00:26:49,821
(His fatherly love wasn't deep enough.)

626
00:26:49,821 --> 00:26:50,821
Have composure.

627
00:26:51,121 --> 00:26:53,931
You cook with low heat and composure.

628
00:26:56,461 --> 00:26:58,971
I always ruin my dishes due to my lack of patience.

629
00:27:02,471 --> 00:27:04,000
There's a specific dish I can make.

630
00:27:04,001 --> 00:27:05,740
Dishes that turn out nicely, even when I'm impatient.

631
00:27:05,741 --> 00:27:06,840
(Confessing her impatience)

632
00:27:06,841 --> 00:27:08,181
You know, dishes like this.

633
00:27:09,441 --> 00:27:12,881
But this requires a relaxed mind.

634
00:27:13,111 --> 00:27:14,181
So, I'm not so good at it.

635
00:27:16,551 --> 00:27:19,251
Now, I fold it.

636
00:27:19,391 --> 00:27:20,391
Take this and...

637
00:27:20,391 --> 00:27:21,391
(Shivering)

638
00:27:23,461 --> 00:27:24,930
Fold it like this.

639
00:27:24,931 --> 00:27:25,991
(She folds it with care.)

640
00:27:28,401 --> 00:27:29,600
(Whatever.)

641
00:27:29,601 --> 00:27:30,701
Move it over there.

642
00:27:31,571 --> 00:27:32,631
And then...

643
00:27:33,501 --> 00:27:34,701
Don't people usually fold it the other way?

644
00:27:35,541 --> 00:27:36,801
No!

645
00:27:36,871 --> 00:27:39,371
(She put care into it, but it ripped.)

646
00:27:39,871 --> 00:27:41,481
Did you ruin the first rolled omelet?

647
00:27:47,211 --> 00:27:48,251
We'll eat it.

648
00:27:49,251 --> 00:27:50,321
Give me a moment.

649
00:27:52,651 --> 00:27:53,950
Take your time.

650
00:27:53,951 --> 00:27:54,961
(Repairing the broken part)

651
00:27:55,691 --> 00:27:58,761
I majored in design in high school.

652
00:27:59,291 --> 00:28:01,501
So, I'm pretty confident...

653
00:28:01,561 --> 00:28:03,631
in shaping things.

654
00:28:06,431 --> 00:28:08,440
This can always be fixed.

655
00:28:08,441 --> 00:28:09,600
(Successfully fixed)

656
00:28:09,601 --> 00:28:11,040
That looks pretty good.

657
00:28:11,041 --> 00:28:12,071
- The rolled omelet.
- Does it?

658
00:28:13,041 --> 00:28:14,111
It smells amazing.

659
00:28:15,781 --> 00:28:17,341
Okay!

660
00:28:17,511 --> 00:28:21,051
(Her rolled omelet is finished, and the main chef approves.)

661
00:28:28,921 --> 00:28:30,891
- Please be cooked all the way.
- Please.

662
00:28:34,591 --> 00:28:36,701
At least, it looks like a proper rolled omelet.

663
00:28:37,331 --> 00:28:39,300
Should we open the lunch boxes now?

664
00:28:39,301 --> 00:28:40,301
(Potato Teacher's gimbap)

665
00:28:40,302 --> 00:28:42,201
- Pack them nicely, please.
- Okay.

666
00:28:43,701 --> 00:28:46,341
Distribute them evenly for everyone.

667
00:28:47,841 --> 00:28:49,741
This is really good young radish kimchi.

668
00:28:50,311 --> 00:28:52,111
Is this what it's like to have kids?

669
00:28:53,781 --> 00:28:55,921
- There are so many kids.
- Generously...

670
00:28:56,381 --> 00:28:57,421
I'm generously...

671
00:28:57,851 --> 00:28:58,951
giving out our kimchi.

672
00:29:01,321 --> 00:29:02,460
All of it!

673
00:29:02,461 --> 00:29:03,891
(She gives all of it.)

674
00:29:05,261 --> 00:29:07,761
Packing box lunches for seven kids...

675
00:29:08,131 --> 00:29:09,131
is not easy.

676
00:29:10,661 --> 00:29:13,831
(They automatically bend down, thinking about the children.)

677
00:29:15,841 --> 00:29:16,871
Make hearts.

678
00:29:17,171 --> 00:29:19,671
- What? We don't have time for that.
- Heart-shaped.

679
00:29:20,541 --> 00:29:22,640
- We don't have time for that.
- Draw hearts!

680
00:29:22,641 --> 00:29:25,610
- We may have to take the ketchup.
- No, draw hearts!

681
00:29:25,611 --> 00:29:27,650
- How would I draw hearts?
- Draw hearts!

682
00:29:27,651 --> 00:29:29,280
- We don't have time for that.
- Just do it.

683
00:29:29,281 --> 00:29:30,620
I would have already finished it by now.

684
00:29:30,621 --> 00:29:32,021
(Maybe there were 8 kids, not 7.)

685
00:29:33,051 --> 00:29:34,521
Heart.

686
00:29:37,221 --> 00:29:38,490
You're driving me insane.

687
00:29:38,491 --> 00:29:39,661
I can't do it.

688
00:29:39,761 --> 00:29:41,391
- Is this ours?
- Yes.

689
00:29:42,431 --> 00:29:45,601
(The broken gimbap goes to the parents.)

690
00:29:45,831 --> 00:29:47,230
That's good enough, right?

691
00:29:47,231 --> 00:29:48,231
(Today's box lunches are finished.)

692
00:29:48,232 --> 00:29:50,170
- I'll wash up now.
- Okay.

693
00:29:50,171 --> 00:29:51,201
I won't take long.

694
00:29:51,941 --> 00:29:52,970
No!

695
00:29:52,971 --> 00:29:55,681
(They're on recess at school.)

696
00:29:58,551 --> 00:30:00,881
- Is that for the show?
- Yes.

697
00:30:02,681 --> 00:30:04,251
Red light.

698
00:30:06,151 --> 00:30:08,321
Eun Soo, you're very interested in cameras.

699
00:30:08,721 --> 00:30:10,390
- Yes.
- Do you like filming?

700
00:30:10,391 --> 00:30:11,421
Yes.

701
00:30:12,361 --> 00:30:14,231
It's not filming anything.

702
00:30:15,031 --> 00:30:16,431
It is.

703
00:30:17,161 --> 00:30:18,230
Is it this one?

704
00:30:18,231 --> 00:30:20,271
(She even checks the unattended cameras.)

705
00:30:20,901 --> 00:30:21,901
What's that?

706
00:30:22,171 --> 00:30:24,941
It has cute, sparkly eyes.

707
00:30:26,971 --> 00:30:29,811
(She easily draws a self-portrait.)

708
00:30:31,711 --> 00:30:34,081
(She was born with the facial expression acting.)

709
00:30:34,611 --> 00:30:38,151
Mom, film my fox song.

710
00:30:39,551 --> 00:30:41,891
(Extraordinary dancing)

711
00:30:43,461 --> 00:30:46,791
(The best singing)

712
00:30:47,991 --> 00:30:52,071
(Eun Soo is an all-around entertainer.)

713
00:30:53,466 --> 00:30:56,175
Please loosen your seatbelt before you get out.

714
00:30:56,176 --> 00:30:57,976
- I'll get your bags.
- Let's go!

715
00:30:58,546 --> 00:31:02,546
- Hi!
- Hi!

716
00:31:03,246 --> 00:31:04,686
Did you rent this place?

717
00:31:05,146 --> 00:31:06,885
Isn't it beautiful?

718
00:31:06,886 --> 00:31:08,285
It's like a hanok village.

719
00:31:08,286 --> 00:31:09,685
It's hanok.

720
00:31:09,686 --> 00:31:11,786
- Are there ginkgo nuts?
- There are.

721
00:31:12,086 --> 00:31:13,625
The ginkgo leaves are gorgeous!

722
00:31:13,626 --> 00:31:15,225
You can sit wherever you want now.

723
00:31:15,226 --> 00:31:16,525
- I want to sit here.
- I'll sit here.

724
00:31:16,526 --> 00:31:18,425
- Kids!
- Yes?

725
00:31:18,426 --> 00:31:21,395
Should we eat our box lunch now?

726
00:31:21,396 --> 00:31:22,396
- Yes!
- Yes!

727
00:31:22,397 --> 00:31:24,935
- I'm hungry!
- I'm so excited.

728
00:31:24,936 --> 00:31:26,165
I wonder what's inside.

729
00:31:26,166 --> 00:31:28,405
- I hope you enjoy it.
- Okay!

730
00:31:28,406 --> 00:31:30,175
Everyone gets a box lunch!

731
00:31:30,176 --> 00:31:31,546
It's a two-tier box?

732
00:31:31,776 --> 00:31:33,506
- Can we open it?
- Of course.

733
00:31:33,606 --> 00:31:34,715
Let's open it.

734
00:31:34,716 --> 00:31:36,675
It has two tiers, so be careful.

735
00:31:36,676 --> 00:31:37,816
- Really?
- Yes.

736
00:31:38,686 --> 00:31:40,016
Awesome!

737
00:31:41,216 --> 00:31:43,725
(The acting class students love it.)

738
00:31:43,726 --> 00:31:45,355
It looks so tasty.

739
00:31:45,356 --> 00:31:47,826
- Rolled omelet.
- Thank you for the food!

740
00:31:47,926 --> 00:31:49,656
Thank you for the food!

741
00:31:51,096 --> 00:31:52,566
(Enjoying)

742
00:31:53,566 --> 00:31:55,835
It's tuna gimbap.

743
00:31:55,836 --> 00:31:57,666
Yes. I love tuna gimbap.

744
00:31:57,806 --> 00:32:00,436
I'm going to eat two pieces at once.

745
00:32:01,476 --> 00:32:03,635
(Putting in)

746
00:32:03,636 --> 00:32:05,105
Don't overdo it, though.

747
00:32:05,106 --> 00:32:06,305
Chew slowly.

748
00:32:06,306 --> 00:32:08,146
(Smiling)

749
00:32:09,246 --> 00:32:11,216
(Chewing)

750
00:32:11,346 --> 00:32:13,416
Eun Soo, how are those rolled omelets?

751
00:32:14,086 --> 00:32:15,155
Delicious.

752
00:32:15,156 --> 00:32:17,085
Right? I made proper rolled omelets...

753
00:32:17,086 --> 00:32:18,856
for the first time in my life.

754
00:32:18,956 --> 00:32:20,356
Give me a high five.

755
00:32:20,456 --> 00:32:21,456
(High five)

756
00:32:21,996 --> 00:32:23,296
Enjoy it.

757
00:32:23,496 --> 00:32:24,925
The ones for teachers...

758
00:32:24,926 --> 00:32:26,495
Oh, my, Ms. Kim!

759
00:32:26,496 --> 00:32:27,496
Oh, my gosh.

760
00:32:27,996 --> 00:32:29,135
Oh, no.

761
00:32:29,136 --> 00:32:32,966
The ones for teachers are even more special.

762
00:32:33,106 --> 00:32:34,106
Do you see it?

763
00:32:34,107 --> 00:32:35,376
(Broken gimbap and leftover ingredients)

764
00:32:35,476 --> 00:32:36,736
- Ha Yun!
- Yes?

765
00:32:36,836 --> 00:32:38,045
Ha Yun, do you want ham?

766
00:32:38,046 --> 00:32:39,106
- No, thanks.
- No.

767
00:32:39,276 --> 00:32:41,046
- Do you want cucumbers?
- No.

768
00:32:42,046 --> 00:32:44,346
Ha Yun, do you want eggs?

769
00:32:45,416 --> 00:32:46,446
No.

770
00:32:48,916 --> 00:32:50,556
- Ha Yun...
- Ha Yun,

771
00:32:50,856 --> 00:32:51,955
- are you sad?
- No.

772
00:32:51,956 --> 00:32:52,956
- Are you feeling all right?
- Yes.

773
00:32:52,957 --> 00:32:54,196
I guess you have enough.

774
00:32:56,126 --> 00:32:58,626
(Quiet)

775
00:32:58,926 --> 00:33:00,425
That was the only one not made by us.

776
00:33:00,426 --> 00:33:02,466
- I finished it.
- No way!

777
00:33:03,966 --> 00:33:05,366
Have you been chewing that this whole time?

778
00:33:06,066 --> 00:33:09,035
Kyung Mo tried to eat 2 pieces in 1 mouthful...

779
00:33:09,036 --> 00:33:10,806
- and has been chewing until now.
- Until now.

780
00:33:10,876 --> 00:33:11,945
Kyung Mo,

781
00:33:11,946 --> 00:33:13,845
you only had two pieces of gimbap.

782
00:33:13,846 --> 00:33:15,076
Do you want some more?

783
00:33:16,116 --> 00:33:18,116
- Should we try some more?
- Yes.

784
00:33:19,416 --> 00:33:22,055
You don't have to.

785
00:33:22,056 --> 00:33:23,286
(We're not forcing you.)

786
00:33:23,456 --> 00:33:25,486
(Okay!)

787
00:33:25,586 --> 00:33:27,456
Ju Eun, what's your favorite in the box lunch?

788
00:33:28,726 --> 00:33:29,796
This one.

789
00:33:29,956 --> 00:33:30,996
Like this?

790
00:33:31,126 --> 00:33:32,126
The chicken nuggets?

791
00:33:32,127 --> 00:33:33,326
(Nodding)

792
00:33:34,436 --> 00:33:36,136
(Laughing)

793
00:33:36,196 --> 00:33:38,306
- Why?
- Ju Eun's favorite is the nuggets.

794
00:33:38,906 --> 00:33:40,535
I tried to eat it, and...

795
00:33:40,536 --> 00:33:41,705
I'm done.

796
00:33:41,706 --> 00:33:44,076
That's the only one that the air fryer made.

797
00:33:44,246 --> 00:33:45,806
That was the only one not made by us.

798
00:33:46,076 --> 00:33:47,105
(One more chicken nugget)

799
00:33:47,106 --> 00:33:48,415
- Ha Yun!
- Yes?

800
00:33:48,416 --> 00:33:49,746
The tuna gimbap...

801
00:33:49,946 --> 00:33:53,446
had savory tuna inside, so it was delicious.

802
00:33:54,456 --> 00:33:55,816
The nuggets were...

803
00:33:56,416 --> 00:33:58,225
really juicy.

804
00:33:58,226 --> 00:33:59,485
(Juicy)

805
00:33:59,486 --> 00:34:00,726
What was your favorite?

806
00:34:01,996 --> 00:34:03,155
Nuggets.

807
00:34:03,156 --> 00:34:05,696
